<tool id="simple-linear-regression" name="Simple linear regression">
    <requirements>
        <requirement type="package" version="1.11.4">r-data.table</requirement>
    </requirements>
    <command detect_errors="exit_code"><![CDATA[
        Rscript '$__tool_directory__/LinearRegression.R' '$input' '$dependantVar' '$explanatoryVar'
        '$output1' '$output2' ]]>
    </command>
    <inputs>
        <param format="tabular,csv" name="input" type="data" label="Input file" help="csv or tabular" />
        <param name="dependantVar" type="integer" value="1" label="Dependant variable (Y)" />
        <param name="explanatoryVar" type="integer" value="1" label="Explanatory variable (X)" />
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
        <data format="png" name="output1" from_work_dir="output-plot.png" />
        <data format="txt" name="output2" from_work_dir="mod-summary.txt" />
    </outputs>
    <help><![CDATA[

.. class:: infomark

This tool performs a linear regression on the data:
 1. you choose your dataset
 2. you choose the variables
     1. the dependant variable (Y)
     2. the explanatory variable (X)

This tool gives two outputs
    1. A scatterplot of the variables and the regression line
    2. The outputs from the model

    ]]></help>
</tool>
